&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Game Seven, we believe best-in-class social creative spans everything from stunty ideas to perfectly timed reaction posts, culturally fluent memes, and timely comments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Social Creative Director leads creative output across all social work streams — concepts, copy, video, static, motion — and isn&#39;t afraid to roll up their sleeves to get it done. This role demands sharp art direction, strong concepting instincts, and the ability to personally execute at a high level while also guiding a team. You set the creative standard not just by giving notes, but by showing what great looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone with a bias toward action, who&#39;s led large-scale social creative at an agency before and brings that experience to Game Seven. You&#39;re a maker first and a leader second, someone who can concept an idea in the morning, art direct a shoot in the afternoon, and review a high volume of social deliverables before EOD. You champion collaboration, uphold strong creative processes, and push for work that breaks through. Most importantly, you take a hands-on role in ensuring the highest quality output and establishing strong narrative throughlines for the everyday content that builds brands over time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
